# AI / RAG Engineering

AI logic lives in dedicated NestJS modules — never scattered across controllers or frontends.

## Module Boundaries

```text
apps/api/src/modules/ai/        # LLM calls, prompt assembly, streaming
apps/api/src/modules/rag/       # chunking, embedding, retrieval
apps/api/src/modules/knowledge/ # document ingestion, storage refs
```

## Conventions

- Abstract LLM providers behind an interface (OpenAI first; multi-provider later).
- **Token budget** — trim context, summarize history, cache embeddings.
- RAG: chunk with overlap, store vectors, retrieve top-k with score threshold.
- Stream responses via SSE; handle client disconnect gracefully.
- Log prompt metadata — never log full user documents or secrets.

## Cost & Performance

- Cache embeddings for unchanged documents.
- Batch embedding jobs in background workers.
- Use the smallest model that meets quality for each task.
- Set max tokens and timeout limits on all AI calls.

## Do Not

- Send unfiltered user content directly to prompts without sanitization.
- Block HTTP threads on long embedding or ingestion jobs.
- Store API keys in code or expose them to the frontend.
